  <Placemark>
    <name>Jeremiah Hamilton House</name>
    <description><![CDATA[<b>Address:</b> 1101 Red River, Austin<br/><br/><b>Marker Text:</b> Born about 1839 in Tennessee, Jeremiah Hamilton was one of nine black representatives in the 12th Texas legislature, 1869-71. He bought this lot on Waller Creek in 1871 and began building this oddly shaped stone structure to house his grocery store. Italian-born Michael Paggi owned the property from 1873 to 1881. He was involved in several unusual business ventures, including the manufacture of ice. (1978)]]></description>
    <Point><coordinates>-97.735017,30.271431,0</coordinates></Point>
